This dish works for a family supper or casual dinner with friends. The honey is the element that softens the meat so you can use this same marinade with skirt steak but would be best if you increased the marinade time to overnight in the frig. Take the meat out from the frig an hour or so before cooking regardless of the cut of meat or length of marinade. I think two hours is a bit short, have done up to five and had great results. Low sodium soy sauce is preferred. If you only have regular soy sauce then cut it with a little water and cut out the salt. You can always salt it on the grill if you feel you need it. This receipe is very similar to one that was in Too Busy to Cook but the fresh rosemary in this one rocks. I always double the receipe for each flank steak so that they are immersed in liquid. A question for others, I used supermarket honey, does the brand of honey itself make a difference? Would it be different with clover or wild flower verses the blend? Would love to know if anyone has experimented.

