I have made this marinade for years and people I serve it to become instantly addicted! It works well on pork and lamb chops too. I have done a few variations and my favorite is to substitute Hoisin (Chinese sweet plum) sauce for the honey and add a little toasted sesame seed oil. The soy sauce is really all the salt you need. Forget adding any more because this has SOOO much flavor already. MY BEST TIP...Marinade overnight! MY SECOND BEST TIP...also marinade some whole Portobello mushooms caps and cook everything on the grill with some soaked apple wood chips. You will end up craving the flavor!

